The paper deals with the problem of Event Schema Induction (ESI) which involves identifying schemas of events from a corpus of documents. This is a natural language processing (NLP) task and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The proposed method TFB involves tensor factorization, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.AI) and data mining (cs.DB). The paper also mentions solving a constrained clique problem, which is a graph theory problem and falls under the category of algorithms (cs.DS) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper deals with building domain-specific knowledge graphs, which is a topic of interest in both NLP and machine learning, making cs.LG a likely category as well.
